<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-19T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–1949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-19T18:00:00+01:00">October
                                    19, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 19—2:46 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3297. Depcirtel October 12, 11 a. m. Secretary General Foreign Office has
                            assured me Italian Government (reference 1335, May 6) does not propose
                            independent action re recognition Chinese Communist regime without prior
                            consultation US. He would appreciate having as soon as possible any
                            further views that we may have in that regard.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>